\begin_layout Standard
Several conditions make Victoria vulnerable to bushfires.
 First of all, this state is the most densely populated and urbanised in
 Australia 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "Bryant2008"

\end_inset

.
 Although it only covers 5% of its territory 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "Luke1978"

\end_inset

, 24.7% of Australia's population lives here 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "Bryant2008"

\end_inset

.
 Additionally, forest cover one-third of its territory 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "Luke1978"

\end_inset

.
 The fire-prone vegetation of the genus Eucalyptus—family Mytaceae— dominate
 these forests 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "Williams2012"

\end_inset

.
 This region also has an extended fire season.
 Victoria's fire regime comprises the austral summer season December-February
 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "Luke1978,BoM2009"

\end_inset

 (see Figure 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:Fire-seasons-in-Australia"

\end_inset

).
 During these months bushfire activity is more intense.
 Although, significant bushfires can also occur in November, March and April.
