\begin_layout Subsubsection
Ecuador
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Bushfires occur in three geographical regions of Ecuador (citation).
 However, the Ecuadorian Andes endures most of the bushfire occurrences
 (citation).
 This region has large extensions of introduced Eucalyptus forests 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "Anchaluisa2013"

\end_inset

.
 Thus, the availability of fuels makes it the most wildfire-prone region.
 The fire season in the Ecuadorian Andes spans from July to November 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "SecretariadeAmbiente2013"

\end_inset

.
 Yet, the most critical months are July, August and September 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "Estacio2012,SecretariadeAmbiente2013"

\end_inset

.
 The coast and the Galapagos Islands experience wildfire episodes from January
 to May 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "SecretariadeAmbiente2013"

\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Wildfires produce severe impacts in Ecuador.
 Yet, information about these impacts is scarce and disperse.
 Wildfires produced 21.570 Ha of area burnt in Ecuador in 2012 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "MinisteriodelAmbiente2013"

\end_inset

.
 The Metropolitan District of Quito (MDQ) is particularly vulnerable to
 wildfires.
 The vulnerability is high because 15.4% of the national population lives
 here.
 Additionally, vegetation covers 60.46 percent of its territory 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "SecretariadeAmbiente2013"

\end_inset

.
 Wildfires destroyed 2700 Ha of the MDQ vegetation in 2009 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "Estacio2012"

\end_inset

.
 In 2012, the area burnt by wildfires increased to 4.882,16 Ha 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "SecretariadeAmbiente2013"

\end_inset

.
 This wildfire season cost the MDQ more than 50 million dollars 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "SecretariadeAmbiente2013"

\end_inset

.
 In 2015, extreme bushfires occured again in Quito killing three firefighters
 (see http://www.elcomercio.com/actualidad/quito-bombero-muerte-incendio-puembo.htm
l).
 Figure 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:Bushfire-in-the-urban-rural-interface-of-Quito"

\end_inset

 depict the magnitude of these fires.
